text: Experience stylish main floor living in this charming three-bedroom, two-bathroom home nestled in one of Lyndens newer established neighborhoods. Revel in the bright, open concept main living space, accentuated by a gourmet kitchen, while the upper-level bonus room invites endless possibilities for utilization. Attention to detail is noticeable blending rustic and modern elements seamlessly with exquisite granite, custom tile work, and classic features throughout. The inviting primary suite boasts a luxurious bathroom and a slider that leads to a serene outdoor oasis with a hot tub and expansive private backyard. Spacious laundry area features an oversized W/D, a utility sink, and ample storage. This home is a must see and wont last!

INVESTORS, CONTRACTORS & those looking to build equity quickly: This AS-IS SALE is the opportunity you've been waiting for. Cordata 3-bedroom 2.5 bath home needs cosmetic restoring to its full glory. Open Layout w/hardwood cabinets, granite counters, stainless appliances, white oak flooring, 9-foot ceilings, primary bedroom w/en suite bath on the main floor, 2-car attached garage, gazebo-covered patio in back yard. Priced for you to budget a paint & carpet remodel including some sheetrock repair, replacement of seveal doors/trim, restore the landscaping, & you can create an exceptional single family home with an remodeled value of $600K or more based on comparable sales / square footage. (HOME IS OCCUPIED! PLS RESPECT OCCUPANTS PRIVACY.)

Custom designed home captures views of Mt. Baker & Twin Sisters. Magnificent one level, 3 bdrm, 2.5 bath home w/ attention to details & quality finishes, award winning builders personal home. Alder wood cabinets, granite counter tops, hardwood floors & vaulted ceilings create a well lit space. Picture windows offer mountain views. Kitchen w/ large island, floor to ceiling pantry, large counters. Other features are gallery/bonus room, double-sided gas FP, upper rec room w/ panoramic mountain views. Spacious 3 car garage has electric car plug in & office. Commercial grade insulated 42x60 shop w/ RV space & septic h/up, office & half bath. 2-12x14 doors/1-12x12. Buyer to verify zoning for potential business. Private oasis, 15 mins to Bham.

Enjoy a lake view in the highly coveted Geneva neighborhood. Lots of natural light in this charming, vintage 1950's property on an oversized lot. Bring some serious elbow grease, and make it your home. Lots of room to add another bedroom. Kitty corner from Geneva elementary school. Big daylight basement is partially finished. Relax and entertain, or dine al fresco on your deck with a beautiful view. So many options for this well loved home that just needs a lot of TLC. Property is sold as-is.

Beautifully updated home in the heart of Bellingham. Centrally located near Barkley Village & Whatcom Falls Park. Walk out your front door to enjoy access to Rail Road trail & a number of parks. Open & inviting floor plan with vaulted ceiling & a wall of windows to enjoy natural light & Bellingham sunsets all year round. Recent updates include laminate floors throughout, quartz countertops, kitchen cabinets, & light fixtures. Roof, & windows recently replaced. Fully Fenced flat back yard with brand new double tier composite deck, perfect for entertaining rain or shine. Turn key home in an ideal location make this a truly remarkable opportunity for anyone looking to settle into their dream home effortlessly.

Rare opportunity: a quiet country home & BUILDABLE LOT! Enjoy the peace and quiet of your own private 5 acre retreat on a dead end county road. Home features: 3 bedrooms, hardwood floors, large living room with vaulted ceiling & an expansive covered deck w/ fossilized stone. Outside is a delight: a spacious lawn surrounds the home, numerous fruit trees and a barn & outbuildings to support your hobbies or store your toys. Property features a RARE buildable lot to enjoy as is or to build into your special legacy property. Buildable lot features: independent power meter and septic tank, driveway, concrete pad for immediate RV parking, tiny home or ADU. The quiet country is calling you - must see in person!

Ground level Condo, Great VRBO! Garden level (Salt Spring) unit at Jacob's Landing. West facing, 1 bedroom, 1 bath - only moments from the beach, and is surrounded by the beautifully landscaped grounds of Jacob's Landing. Features include new laminate wood flooring, all furnishings and appliances stay. Enjoy all the amenities Jacob's Landing has to offer: Indoor heated pool, hot tub, tennis court, great beach access, and much more. Area features hard sand tide flats, fantastic beach, great crabbing & clamming! 1 hour to Mt Baker ski slopes and hiking trails!

Located in Bellinghams beautiful Geneva neighborhood the split-level home boasts 1, 634 square feet, featuring 3 beds, 2 baths, and a tranquil running brook on its expansive cul-de-sac lot spanning 11, 771 square feet. Built in 1979, it seamlessly combines timeless charm with modern comforts. The main level welcomes with a spacious living area, while the adjacent kitchen overlooks the dining area, perfect for entertaining. Outside, enjoy the soothing sounds of the running brook amidst the lush surroundings. Don't miss the opportunity to call this serene property yours. Schedule your showing today!

This single story gem on .55 acres offers 3 bedrooms, 2 baths and a detached 30x36 heated shop with an 18x36 lean-to. Renovated with new kitchen, flooring and paint inside and out, it exudes modern charm. The primary suite boasts an updated bathroom with a luxurious tile shower and glass doors, alongside a large walk-in closet and access to outdoor patio area. A pellet stove adds coziness to the living room. Enjoy outdoor tranquility with garden space, a small orchard with pear and apple trees, and ample room for hobbies or storage in the shop. The railway behind the home is not an active rail. Property owner has use of railroad right-of-way space for personal use.

Enjoy living in the heart of Bellingham in this luxurious 2 bed/2 bath condo across the street from Laurel Park. This ground floor unit is within walking distance to Western Washington University, downtown pubs, restaurants, shops, trails and the waterfront. Beautiful custom kitchen cabinets, granite countertops and stainless-steel appliances. Washer/dryer included with the sale. (Washer is just one year old!) Unit has been pre-inspected! The gas fireplace is a great way to get cozy on chilly nights. Sip a glass of wine on the patio and enjoy summer warmth and park views. Radiant heat, separate storage area and assigned uncovered parking. Perfect for first time buyers or as a second home getaway! Enjoy the ultimate urban lifestyle!
Large treed lot on quiet Windsor Dr in the heart of Point Roberts. Come enjoy the peace and tranquility of Point Roberts! Lot 4.

This charming turnkey bungalow, nestled in the Puget neighborhood, comes fully updated both inside & out. Featuring main-level living w/ primary suite & attached bathroom on the first floor & a versatile 2nd bedroom or flex space located in the daylight basement. The spacious floor plan is complemented by a large picture window that soaks the living & dining area in natural light. Newer appliances including gas range, microwave, dishwasher & washer/dryer, & new carpeting. It has been completely repainted inside & out. Additional updates include new bathroom vanity, new lighting throughout, newer comp roof, new HW tank, & newly fenced backyard w/ refreshed landscaping. Minutes to amenities & downtown. This home is a gem, & is ready to go!

Nestled in the enchanting Whatcom Falls neighborhood, this charming single-level home offers 2 beds, 1 bath, and 1, 023sf of tastefully updated living space. Close to Galbraith, Whatcom Falls Park, Lafeens Donuts and Davinci's Market you're in a very central location with easy access to Downtown while also being close to some of Bellingham's most sought after outdoor destinations. Features include stainless steel appliances, kitchen with dinning area, updated bath with new skylight, tile flooring, detached oversized garage, and a partially covered back deck with sunken hot tub. Enjoy The Alley of Dreams shared for neighborly gatherings. Experience the essence of community charm in this delightful residence!

New construction home with Mountain View in the lakeside and golf course community of Sudden Valley! Flat driveway with no steps leading to the front door. Large primary suite features a fireplace, spacious bathroom with a free standing tub, walk-in-closet, & its own private access to the deck. Everything is on the main floor: kitchen, dinning, family, primary & laundry room! Beautiful modern kitchen with wood grain cabinets open to the dinning & living room area. Quartz counter tops, SS LG appliances, & under cabinet lighting. Vinyl Planked flooring throughout the entire home (no carpet). Home features a heat pump (heat & AC). Enjoy the amazing views from the double deck. Stairs off lower deck leading to the backyard with mountain view!

Get your start at the Glen with this huge lot in a great location! Across the street from a comfort station and playground, this property currently sleeps 6. Large fire pit area with several wood sheds set up for privacy in the heart of Div 1. Shed on site for extra storage, plenty of room to add a gazebo. Huge covered deck has a spot for your BBQ as well as room to dine out under cover. Updated flooring inside, full bathroom, a bedroom and bunkbeds. Just 15 minutes from the base of Mount Baker as well as Silver Lake. The Glen amenities include two pools, a sauna, hot tub, basketball & tennis courts, two lodges, events & activities, 24/7 security and more. Zoned recreational limited to 120/nights per year occupancy. No rentals allowed.

Affordable rural living - Essentially new home with shop on almost 3/4 of an acre just East of town. Home was completely remodeled / rebuilt 2 years ago. Taken down to the studs. New siding, roof, plumbing, electrical, bathrooms, Kitchen, walls, flooring, appliances and mechanical. You name it - it's likely new. Open great room floor plan in great condition. Very attractive home and efficient with mini split heating and A/C and fully applianced. No need to deal with a well, water is provided from the local water association. Approximately 30X25 foot shop with an attached lean to. Easy care landscaping and gated entrance. This is a great opportunity for a big lot with a like new home and shop at an affordable price.

This lovingly cared for home in a quiet Sudden Valley setting offers comfortable single-level living. Great opportunity for first-time home Buyers, downsizing or investment! Plenty of natural light inside via windows and skylights, and outside, the natural setting is serene and full of wildlife - deer are regular visitors. Open kitchen and dining area with laundry room, cozy living room and three bedrooms. 3/4 bath en-suite to the spacious primary bedroom. Attached carport. Tons of upgrades including a whole-house generator, two ductless mini-split heat pumps, composite decking plus newer dishwasher, washer/dryer, water heater and roof! Community amenities include two pools, beaches, golf course, tennis courts, parks, playgrounds and more!

Come see this desirable new construction home in the Whispering Meadows neighborhood in Nooksack. This 4 bed, 2.25 bath house has an open floor plan, SS appliances, quartz countertops, luxury vinyl plank, fireplace, & vaulted ceilings. Primary bedroom on main floor with large walk-in closet, walk-in shower, and double vanity. Large bedroom above the garage could be used as a bonus room. This house is perfectly positioned on a huge lot backing up to a beautiful nature preserve that no one can build on behind you. Which will allow you to enjoy outdoor entertaining with your covered deck and large backyard. Home is also within walking distance to Nooksack Elementary & Nooksack Middle School. This house is not in the flood zone!

Move right in to this newly renovated home in friendly Ferndale! Beyond its unassuming exterior you'll find a spacious 5-bedroom home including a finished basement with its own entrance. Impressive Mount Baker view from the living room, and modern touches throughout including new flooring & paint, new interior doors & trim, new lighting, & quartz countertops in the kitchen and baths. Just off the living rm, a deck overlooks the huge backyard! The sizable lot offers tons of potential to either subdivide, or build an ADU or detached garage. Possibilities are endless! Plenty of parking including space for an RV or boat. Wired for solar. Great location near schools, eateries, parks, and more. Don't miss out on this rare opportunity in Ferndale!

Beautiful, spacious Darby Estates condo unit, meticulously maintained 1 BR / 1BA + bonus room, with upgraded thick slab granite countertops in kitchen, bath & vanity, plus designer appliances, and custom California closets. Secluded end of the complex with trees and no traffic, ultra quiet top floor. Enjoy sunsets from covered, west-facing balcony accessible by living room and bedroom. Two, covered parking stalls included. Beautiful community clubhouse amenities with kitchen, meeting area and fitness center; security guard at night. Centrally located near Bellis Fair Mall, local restaurants, WCC and more! Affordable HOA includes water, sewer & garbage plus all ext. maintenance. Can be used as a rental and no pet size or weight restriction.

This custom-built single-level home is proudly situated in a lovely development that is a short walk into Fairhaven and the trail system. There are no stairs to enter this home which has wide doorways and halls, vaulted ceilings with skylights, and an open floor plan. There's even a wheelchair-accessible tub/shower in the guest bath and a den that could be the 3rd bedroom. The sellers added an art studio (could be an ADU) off the 3-car garage that's heated and has a powder room. There is also a heated shop space and office down below that is accessible from the rear yard (below the deck). The home is surrounded by a large irrigated lawn with a mature landscape, a large Trex deck, and patio to take in the lovely territorial and sunset views.

Sunnyland cottage with promise! Moments away from Trader Joe's and convenient to all of Bellingham downtown. Bike or walk to everything, from the romantic waterfront to fine restaurants, banks to cozy coffee houses... also near St. Joseph's Hospital, schools and colleges. 3 bedrooms, with vaulted ceilings, plus plenty of backyard space for gardening & BBQ parties. Cute park & playground across the street from front door. Invest in the heart of Bellingham at a rare price for this geographic location. No HOA; thus, no HOA dues! Huge parking pad in front. Quick jump to I-5, so it's a great option for commuters. Home sale includes some items; outbuilding in backyard area. Live on a mellow block, just a hop to Whatcom Library, cafes and theater.

Presenting the epitome of coastal elegance and sophistication in this well-cared for Chuckanut Crest residence, offering breathtaking 180-degree views of the Bay, islands, and mountains. Privacy, tranquility, and security are paramount in this coveted location at the end of the road, yet is just minutes from historic Fairhaven & town. Witness the enchanting spectacle of whales & sea life from the large entertaining deck, while eagles gracefully soar at eye level. Step inside to discover a wealth of upscale features, including premium hardwood oak flooring, expansive windows w/ transoms, and impeccable door & trim package. The library, office, heated workspace/shop, & finished basement provide all you need to enjoy the perfect NW lifestyle.

Sought after single-story 4-plex unit in the ideal central Blaine location. Walking distance to schools and downtown core. Easy parking-extra storage-well-managed properties make this a smart investment. Updated with recent improvements/very good condition. Consistent tenants as Blaine is an ideal cross-border location.

Enjoy your home in Snowater Condominiums in close proximately to the Mt. Baker National Forest and the Nooksack River, The home has been remodeled with many updates such as new flooring, kitchen appliances, etc. The Trapper units are next to the recreation building which features an indoor pool, exercise facilities, athletic court, and pickle ball. Also available are tennis courts, bbq area, trails and clubhouse. Condominium is approximately a thirty minute drive to the world famous Mt. Baker Ski area.

Highly sought after Cedar Grove Park 55+ forest setting community w/ a small lake, south Bellingham across street is Lake Padden. Charming w/ some updates 1, 288 SF manu home 1980 currently w/ 2 BR and 3/4 bath & half bath. Could be returned to original 3 BR & 1.75 BA. 2 living rooms. Spacious kitchen w/ eating bar, good sized dining space. Natural gas fireplace. Recent features - new insulation sub floor & above, new ductless heat pump/AC, flooring. Front of the home on one street & then back of the home w/ carport/extra parking, yard, & more private garden area behind the home. Community has a clubhouse, well stocked shop, a small lake & waterfront picnic area. RV parking/storage available within the community. This is a great home!
Large treed lot on quiet Windsor Dr in the heart of Point Roberts. Come enjoy the peace and tranquility of Point Roberts! Lot 5.

This sunny Southside home has been remodeled from top to bottom and feels like a new house. New roof, kitchen, bathrooms, floor coverings, and interior and exterior paint. Fresh and modern with white cabinets and quartz counters. Large primary suite with big walk-in closet. 4th bedroom on lower level with adjacent rec room, full bathroom, storage closets, and separate entrance has great potential for ADU conversion. Cozy in-floor radiant heating. Excellent location is right by the entrance to the Samish Crest Trail. Hiking, swimming, boating, tennis, and golf are nearby at Lake Padden Park, and Galbraith Mountain biking is an easy pedal away. Enjoy the best of Bellingham outdoor recreation right from your doorstep.

Take in the unobstructed views of the mountains and the valley from this home that is better than new! The seller has already installed your fence, all the window coverings and has a good start on additional landscaping. This lovely home boasts a covered back deck and a private backyard that will be great for entertaining. Other features include: two primary bedrooms with attached BRs, gourmet kitchen with large quartz island, large utility room, and two additional BRs + full BA and flex space upstairs.

Welcome to this delightful ground-level condo nestled in the sought-after Darby Estates! This unit offers 1 bedroom, 1 bathroom plus additional office space ideal for remote work or study. Situated in the vibrant Cordata neighborhood, you'll relish easy access to Bellis Fair Mall, Costco, I5, Cordata Park, hospitals & more. With only one owner, this meticulously maintained condo exudes quality & care. Unit features crown molding, walk-in closet, large laundry room, en-suite bathroom & 2 designated parking spots. HOA provides water, sewer & garbage plus access to clubhouse & gym. Whether you're a first-time buyer, downsizing, or seeking an investment opportunity, this condo promises comfortable living in a prime Bellingham locale.

Experience luxury living unlike any other in this exclusive townhome nestled within the highly sought-after Aerie community at Semiahmoo. Enjoy a protected one-of-a-kind waterfront view w/ nearly 671' of frontage, where sunrises greet you off Mt. Baker in the morning to the twilight cityscape of White Rock, BC at night. Secluded within a private enclave of only 11 townhomes, life at Aerie ensures a serene & tranquil setting. Classic build w/ freshly painted interior offers a timeless design featuring vaulted ceilings, open plate glass windows, functional main floor living, & wrap-around deck w/ multiple seating areas. Beach access is just steps away along w/ miles of walking/biking trails & the iconic Semiahmoo Resort Golf & Spa.

Experience effortless one-level living in this move-in ready gem with views! Situated in the growing King Mountain neighborhood, this corner lot residence offers privacy and space, ensuring tranquility away from neighbors. Step inside this expansive rambler to discover upgraded quartz countertops gracing the open kitchen, complemented by sprawling hardwood floors and contemporary custom finishes throughout. Stay comfortable year-round with an energy-efficient design featuring a heat pump for cooling, a high-efficiency furnace, and an on-demand water heater. Western and southern exposures, with partial bay views from the living area, kitchen, and primary bedroom. Don't miss out on the opportunity to call this one-of-a-kind home yours!

Explore this well-maintained, stunning 2, 110 sqft rambler, featuring 3 bed/2 baths and located on a dead end cul-de-sac. New roof in 2014, and recently painted exterior. The primary suite offers a lavish walk-in shower, jetted tub, and expansive walk-in closet. Seamlessly blend indoor and outdoor living through a glass slider from the dining room, opening onto a fabulous covered back deck, perfect for entertaining year-round, and fun playhouse! Long driveway offers plenty of parking, and additional parking in front of the home. Conveniently located near Cornwall Park, Bellis Fair Mall, Fred Meyers, and Whatcom Community College, with easy freeway access for seamless commuting. Live the Bellingham lifestyle with I-5 just minutes away!

Investor alert! Motivated seller, bring your offers!! Peaceful and relaxing, light-filled adorable home. Panoramic views of mountains and green space. Huge closet in primary bedroom, nearly new SS appliances, an open-concept kitchen this place has it all! Enjoy your morning coffee on the sunny deck overlooking the delightful duck pond. Furry friends welcome :) Close to restaurants, medical clinics, and shopping. Cozy fire for a cold night. Well cared for, with many upgrades. A/C, storm doors, engineered hardwood, extra storage, plenty of parking. Professional and organized HOA. Live a comfortable life at an affordable price. This could be a great investment opportunity with rentals approved and no cap.

Gentle sloping building lot located in the lakeside and golf course community of Sudden Valley. Public services include: water, sewer, electricity, natural gas, cable, phone. Design options include a single level home with garage below; or a 2 story home with garage down. This property is level off of the road, with very easy access off of Marigold Dr. - expect a flat driveway here. The property slopes upward in the rear of the property. This is a high quality residential vacant lot. The gate-2 neighborhood is the same entrance to the golf course, Lake Louise trail, recreation area and Morning and Afternoon beaches (neighborhood waterfront parks / beaches).

Welcome home to your private waterfront retreat on beautiful Lake Samish! This gem has stunning lake & mountain views throughout, including in the 1, 016 sf unfinished basement! Inside, you'll find 2 updated kitchens with quartz counters, new appliances, 2 living rooms, a rec room, updated luxury vinyl plank flooring & more. Outside, you'll find a huge private dock, beautiful beachfront, boat lift, multiple decks & an additional lot with extra storage. The home could be enjoyed as one residence, multi-generational living or possibly a separate MIL suite with its own separate entrance, kitchen, bathroom, deck & washer/dryer. Rare opportunity to own a lakefront home that doesn't require flood insurance. Perfect timing for summer!

Welcome Home. This studio unit has been lightly lived in and in great condition. This is on floor one with patio access to the lawn area. You will enjoy the patio and the beautiful views of the creek and trails. Reserved parking place close to the stairs for easy access. Affordable living.

Location, location, location! Home in the heart of Lynden. Steps away from Lynden City Park and the Kaemingk Trail. Great 4 bedroom home on a culdesac with a large, very private backyard. 2, 015 SF, try-level with laundry on lower level. Schedule a visit!

Find peace and serenity in this lovely home as you gaze through the large living room picture windows upon the fir trees of Cornwall Park. Nestled in on a quiet street you will still enjoy the convenience of being in the core of Bellingham with easy walking to parks, downtown and I-5 within a one minute drive. The backyard is quite large for a city lot and has plenty of room for playing or gardening with unlimited potential for you to create your backyard sanctuary. Inside you will find original wood floors, a fresh kitchen and a fireplace to cozy up next to. The garage is ready for your projects, hobbies, home storage, a compact car or whatever your needs demand. You will love this wonderful property. Come and see you new home!

Welcome home! This move-in ready 2 level condo consists of 2 large bedrooms and 2.5 bathrooms. With an additional generous loft area and large great room off the main living room, you'll find you have ample space in this 1, 660 sq ft home. Enjoying cooking in the beautifully updated kitchen with quarts countertops and stainless-steel appliances. The condo also has a large laundry room with plenty of cabinets for storage and attached garage. Access the community clubhouse for larger gatherings or enjoy the walking trails in the nearby Bender Fields for some fresh air.

Extraordinary, superbly maintained Birch Bay lifestyle home! Extensive updates, remarkable features in and outside of home. 1, 628 SF/1 level, 3 BR, 1.75 BA w/new flooring, counters, paint, fireplace, bay window dining room, skylight, more... A larger, newly fully fenced, level lot that is like a peninsula - adjacent to greenbelt and RV parking room. Pleasantly landscaped. Garage is large 989 SF with 3 bays, 2 entrances & shop area. New roof w/new solar panels. New siding. New heat pump/AC. Large back deck for entertaining & hot tub. Yard w/ fruit trees, firepit w/rock surrounding & shed. Home faces southeast sun exposure and a view of Mt. Baker. 5 minutes to Birch Bay beaches. 10 minutes to Border. 25 minutes to Bellingham.

WELCOME TO BALFOUR VILLAGE PHASE 2! Affordable living, JUST COMPLETED rambler in a newer community. This cozy home features an open floor plan on a large corner lot with 4 bedrooms, 1.75 baths, 2 car garage, stainless steel appliances, quartz countertops & A/C. Come enjoy tranquil living with peace and quiet and natural surroundings. Only 30 minutes to Bellingham!

This charming 4-bedroom, 3-bathroom farmhouse is nestled on a 1.46 acre lot and surrounded by beautiful grass farm land. Step inside to discover a warm and inviting interior, highlighted by the cozy ambiance of wood-burning fireplaces. The kitchen is updated with beautiful cabinetry, granite countertops and stainless steel appliances. The mature yard and flowerbeds offer beaty and easy maintenance. The large lot offers plenty of space to build a shop or outbuilding to fit your needs! With a perfect mid county location, you will enjoy both the privacy and serenity of the countryside, and easy access to surrounding towns and amenities.

Custom West Coast Shingle style home on 2, 5-acre parcels, designed to maximize view of Mt. Baker and experience privacy and quiet of forest. Natural light from vaulted ceilings illuminates rich fir floors on main level. 2 patios off great room surrounded by gardens. Main floor with guest BR, BR, mudroom, laundry. Upper level MBR has view of Baker, 2 nd BR view of fenced vegetable garden and grape arbor. 1000sf space over garage has bedroom, unfinished BR, office, family room or potential apartment with private entrance. Large workshop with 2 car parking plus covered shed for RV, tractor, equipment.

Welcome home to this one level spotless condo with no steps! You will love the updated laminate plank wood floors & nice and light interior. The living and dining room has nice access to the deck which will make a perfect spot to unwind after a long day or sunny afternoon. The kitchen has nice appliances with solid wood cabinets and ample prep area. It has nice light and bright informal living area. The primary suite features a full bath, walk in closet and private patio area. The second bedroom makes a great guest room or office. There is a separate laundry room. There is a storage unit in carport area and covered parking.

Welcome to your dream home on top of Barkley Hill. Stunning panoramic views of the bay, mountains, and the twinkling city lights as far as the eye can see. Primary living space including 3 bedrooms total on main floor including Kitchen, living, dining room and laundry all with zero steps. Primary bedroom has en-suite bathroom, double sinks, soaking tub, and separate shower and walk in closet. 2 additional bedrooms, 2nd living area, bathroom, and access to patio area located on lower level. Two upper decks facing West for for outdoor enjoyment and sunset viewing. Centrally located within minutes to shopping, restaurants, entertainment, and trail systems. Home boasts ample storage and a hidden gem-a wine cellar. Come see this today.

One of 20 new homes by Skeers Construction in Hannah Creek. This is the ultimate PNW lifestyle location with access to 65+ miles of world class mountain biking, hiking, and trail running on the adjacent 3000 acre Galbraith Mountain trail system. Whatcom Falls Park is just down the street, and downtown is less than 3 miles away. Great lot has nice western sun exposure, sitting on a wooded greenbelt with creek. One-level living with 10' ceilings throughout, and a covered deck for year round outdoor enjoyment. 4 bedrooms, with French doors on one for an ideal home office. Garage has extra depth on one side for a 3rd tandem bay or workshop space. Heat pump for efficient heating and comfortable cooling.

Incredible westerly views of Drayton Harbor and Semiahmoo from this nearly new home in a sweet pocket neighborhood. Access to water is across the street, ensuring that the view will always be protected. Enjoy the scenery from the great room and the primary suite. Air conditioning via both mini-splits and forced air. Fully fenced yard and covered patio through French doors are perfect for entertaining. With easy access to I5 and the Canadian border and only 20 minutes to Bellingham, this move-in ready home has stylish finishes and new interior pain. Stainless entry to main living area and the 3/4 bath and bedroom plus laundry/mudroom/garage allows for main floor living as well.

This spacious home has been loved by the seller since it was brand new...and now it is your turn to enjoy it! The rooms are spacious and it is on one level. Over the years, they added an atrium-type family room with a bar and rec room with cedar siding inside, large skylights, and floor-to-ceiling windows that look out to the manicured landscaping. The appliances have been updated over the years and there is plenty of cabinet and counter storage space as well as a pantry. The living room looks to the east and has a wonderful view over the church parking lot to take in the sunrises each morning. There is a heated shop and a garden shed in the fully fenced rear yard, as well as an attached, oversized 2-vehicle garage.

Panoramic views from every room of this custom-built South Hill home. Street level entry to main living space, gourmet kitchen & 1/2 bath. Second level dedicated to spacious master suite w/adjoining den w/wet bar, expansive bath w/walk in shower & deep soaking tub, huge closet & laundry room. Third level 2 bedrooms, bath & large heated storage. Covered decks all levels. Well-designed plan w/elevator! Fourth level shop/work-out room. Terraced gardens, 2-car garage + off-street parking.

Stunning Barkley Home! Boasting over 3, 700 sqft of living space with thoughtful upgrades throughout, 2 decks, a patio, vaulted ceilings, & a 2 bedroom apartment... this home is sure to impress! Primary bedroom with private deck, walk-in closet & 5 piece spa-like bath. Charming 2-bed basement apartment w/ separate entrance, high ceilings, kitchen, full bath & laundry. Has been rented out for last 10 yrs & has helped pay down the mortgage. Shop space w/ separate entrance & utility sink for hobbies & projects. Fully-fenced & lined with trees - backyard is extremely private & adorned with lush landscaping, green space & firepit. One of Bellinghams most sought after neighborhoods... close to Barkley Village, trail system, & parks. Welcome Home!

Wonderful move in ready townhouse condo in this highly sought after community. New carpet and paint make this 4 bedroom 2.5 bath one you don't want to miss. Lots of privacy yet minutes from Bellingham, Barkely center and easy access to trails to Bloedel Donovan and Whatcom Falls Park. This townhome boasts 4 bedroom, 2.5 bathrooms and lots of space to enjoy Main living area has a nice gas fireplace that opens up to dining area and kitchen. Large private deck off living/dining area ready for outdoor entertaining. Community features include clubhouse, pool, hot tub, sauna, raquetball, tennis/pickleball courts plus water, sewer, garbage and exterior maintenance. Come check it out!
